# --- Unreal Engine generated / per-machine artefacts ---
Binaries/
DerivedDataCache/
Intermediate/
Saved/
Build/

# Plugin build outputs (never commit compiled plugin binaries / intermediates)
Plugins/*/Binaries/
Plugins/*/Intermediate/

# Per-user editor scratch content (developer collections etc.)
Content/Developers/

# NOTE: Content/REBUS/ (BaseLevel.umap + ground materials) IS committed. The
# init_unreal.py builder regenerates it in the editor, but the product launches
# the editor binary in -game mode where that authoring step is skipped (and is
# never run during a cook), so the map/materials must ship in the repo or the
# runtime fails with "map ... could not be found". The builder stays idempotent:
# it only (re)generates these assets when they are absent.

# Python bytecode cache
Content/Python/__pycache__/

# v1.0.130 -- OrbitConnector plugin. In dev workspaces this directory may
# hold only a local build stub (`OrbitConnector.uplugin` with
# `VersionName: 0.0.0-stub` + empty `Modules: []`) plus a vendored
# `ThirdParty/Cli/win-x64/orbit-cli.exe` so UnrealBuildTool can resolve the
# `.uproject`-required plugin reference. The REAL OrbitConnector plugin
# (source + binaries) is restored per-machine before a shipping
# packaged build; neither the stub nor the real plugin belongs in this
# repo (the stub is per-developer scaffolding; the real plugin lives in
# its own git mirror). Excluding the whole subtree keeps both the stub
# AND any partial real-plugin checkout from being accidentally committed.
Plugins/OrbitConnector/

# v1.0.130 -- per-machine plugin Config scratch (editor-generated
# FilterPlugin.ini boilerplate that the UE 5.7 plugin editor drops when
# any operator opens Edit > Plugins > Rebus Visualiser). Pure noise in
# git: the file is empty boilerplate with no project-relevant filter
# entries.
Plugins/*/Config/FilterPlugin.ini

# v1.0.130 -- editor-generated per-developer transient maps subtree
# (Content/REBUS/Maps/_GENERATED/<user>/...) that the UE 5.7 editor
# drops when the operator runs ad-hoc builder utilities. Not part of
# the shipped BaseLevel; per-developer scratch only.
Content/REBUS/Maps/_GENERATED/

# v1.0.130 -- Fab Megascans surface payloads. The pre-v1.0.130 worker tree
# tried Fab "Add to Project" for the floor surface bundles, which lays down
# a sub-tree under Content/Fab/Megascans/Surfaces/<DisplayName_<slug>>/...
# Each tier holds 4-channel 4K/8K Megascans textures (~50-200 MB per
# surface) PLUS Megascans-authored MaterialInstance .uassets. None of that
# belongs in git: the bundles are per-developer caches that are large,
# binary, and irrelevant once v1.0.130 routes the surface delivery through
# the Rebus portal (URebusSurfaceFetcher + /assets/surfaces/<name>/manifest.
# json -- see README v1.0.130). Excluding the whole Fab/ root prevents an
# accidental commit on a workstation where the Fab editor browser has
# previously paid down some surface bundles. Restore on a per-machine basis
# by re-running the Fab editor browser if anyone needs the legacy assets.
Content/Fab/

# Visual Studio / Rider / Xcode IDE files
.vs/
.idea/
.vscode/
*.sln
*.suo
*.opensdf
*.sdf
*.VC.db
*.VC.opendb
*.xcodeproj
*.xcworkspace

# Project descriptor backups (never commit these)
*.uproject.bak*
*.orig-backup
*.uplugin.bak*

# Build logs
*.log

# OS noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
